3. Setting Up Git for Version Control with GitHub
	1. Install Git

		Open a terminal in Ubuntu.
		Run the following commands to check and install Git:
		sudo apt update
		sudo apt install git -y

	2. Configure Git

		Set up your username for Git commits:
			git config --global user.name "Your GitHub Username"

		Set up your email for Git commits:
			git config --global user.email "your-email@example.com"

		Verify the configuration:
			git config --global --list

